{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V5R29o8i9M2asoePp6rpQu","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 20.1: Lane Container & Lane Components\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want to see multiple epic lanes in the TUI during parallel execution,\n11\tso that I can track progress across all active worktrees.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a new `src/lib/ink-lane.tsx`, **when** imported, **then** it exports a `Lane` React component that accepts `LaneProps` (epicId, epicTitle, currentStory, phase, acProgress, storyProgressEntries, driver, cost, elapsedTime) and renders a single lane's status display. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t2. **Given** a new `src/lib/ink-lane-container.tsx`, **when** imported, **then** it exports a `LaneContainer` React component that accepts `LaneContainerProps` (lanes array, terminalWidth) and renders all lanes according to layout rules. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t3. **Given** a terminal width >= 120 columns and 2 active lanes, **when** `LaneContainer` renders, **then** the two lanes display side-by-side (each lane occupying roughly half the terminal width). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t4. **Given** a terminal width between 80 and 119 columns and 2 active lanes, **when** `LaneContainer` renders, **then** the two lanes display stacked vertically in compact mode. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t5. **Given** a terminal width < 80 columns, **when** `LaneContainer` renders, **then** only the single most recently active lane renders in full, and others collapse to one-line summaries. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t6. **Given** each `Lane` component, **when** rendered, **then** it shows: epic title, current story key + phase, a story progress bar (done/in-progress/pending symbols per story), and driver name + cost/time. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t7. **Given** 3 or more active lanes, **when** `LaneContainer` renders at >= 120 cols, **then** lanes 1 and 2 render in full side-by-side, and lanes 3+ collapse to one-line summaries in the format: `Lane N: Epic Title │ story ◆ phase │ $cost / time`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t8. **Given** `max_parallel: 1` (single lane mode), **when** the TUI renders, **then** the display is visually identical to the current single-lane TUI — no `LaneContainer` wrapper visible, no layout changes. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t9. **Given** a `Lane` component receives a `CollapsedLanes` subcomponent, **when** rendered, **then** `CollapsedLanes` accepts an array of collapsed lane data and renders each as a single line with lane index, epic title, current story, phase, cost, and time. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t10. **Given** the `ink-app.tsx` root component, **when** updated to integrate `LaneContainer`, **then** it conditionally renders `LaneContainer` when `laneCount > 1` or renders the existing single-lane layout when `laneCount <= 1`, preserving backward compatibility. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t11. **Given** the `Header` component in `ink-components.tsx`, **when** multiple lanes are active, **then** the header displays lane count and total cost across all lanes (e.g., `codeharness run | 2 lanes | 47m elapsed | $18.60 spent`). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n36\t\n37\t12. **Given** the `LaneContainer` component, **when** the terminal is resized, **then** the layout mode (side-by-side, stacked, single) re-evaluates based on the new terminal width. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n38\t\n39\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n40\t\n41\t- [ ] Task 1: Create `src/lib/ink-lane.tsx` (AC: #1, #6)\n42\t  - [ ] Define `LaneProps` interface with all required fields\n43\t  - [ ] Define `StoryProgressEntry` type: `{ key: string; status: 'done' | 'in-progress' | 'pending' }`\n44\t  - [ ] Implement `Lane` component rendering epic title, current story + phase, story progress bar, driver + cost/time\n45\t  - [ ] Use `✓` for done stories, `◆` for in-progress, `○` for pending in the progress bar\n46\t  - [ ] Format cost as `$X.XX` and elapsed as `Xm` or `Xh Xm`\n47\t\n48\t- [ ] Task 2: Create `src/lib/ink-lane-container.tsx` (AC: #2, #3, #4, #5, #7, #9, #12)\n49\t  - [ ] Define `LaneContainerProps` with `lanes: LaneData[]`, `terminalWidth: number`\n50\t  - [ ] Define `LaneData` interface capturing all per-lane state for rendering\n51\t  - [ ] Implement layout mode calculation: `side-by-side` (>=120), `stacked` (80-119), `single` (<80)\n52\t  - [ ] Render top 2 lanes in full, lanes 3+ via `CollapsedLanes`\n53\t  - [ ] Implement `CollapsedLanes` sub-component: single-line summaries for overflow lanes\n54\t  - [ ] Listen for terminal resize via `process.stdout.columns` to re-evaluate layout\n55\t\n56\t- [ ] Task 3: Integrate into `ink-app.tsx` (AC: #8, #10)\n57\t  - [ ] Add conditional rendering: if `state.lanes && state.lanes.length > 1`, render `LaneContainer`; else render existing single-lane layout\n58\t  - [ ] Ensure zero visual changes when `laneCount <= 1`\n59\t  - [ ] Import `LaneContainer` from `./ink-lane-container.js`\n60\t\n61\t- [ ] Task 4: Extend Header in `ink-components.tsx` (AC: #11)\n62\t  - [ ] Add optional `laneCount` and `totalCost` fields to `SprintInfo`\n63\t  - [ ] Conditionally render lane count in header when `laneCount > 1`\n64\t  - [ ] Format: `codeharness run | {N} lanes | {elapsed} | ${cost}`\n65\t\n66\t- [ ] Task 5: Write unit tests for `src/lib/__tests__/ink-lane.test.tsx` (AC: #1, #6)\n67\t  - [ ] Test: `Lane` renders epic title\n68\t  - [ ] Test: `Lane` renders current story and phase\n69\t  - [ ] Test: `Lane` renders story progress bar with correct symbols\n70\t  - [ ] Test: `Lane` renders driver name, cost, and elapsed time\n71\t  - [ ] Test: `Lane` exports correct types\n72\t\n73\t- [ ] Task 6: Write unit tests for `src/lib/__tests__/ink-lane-container.test.tsx` (AC: #2-#5, #7, #8, #9, #12)\n74\t  - [ ] Test: side-by-side layout when terminalWidth >= 120 and 2 lanes\n75\t  - [ ] Test: stacked layout when terminalWidth 80-119 and 2 lanes\n76\t  - [ ] Test: single-lane layout when terminalWidth < 80\n77\t  - [ ] Test: lanes 3+ collapse to one-line summaries\n78\t  - [ ] Test: single lane mode renders without container wrapper\n79\t  - [ ] Test: collapsed lane format matches `Lane N: Epic Title │ story ◆ phase │ $cost / time`\n80\t  - [ ] Test: layout mode re-evaluates when terminalWidth changes\n81\t\n82\t- [ ] Task 7: Write unit tests for Header extension (AC: #11)\n83\t  - [ ] Test: Header shows lane count when `laneCount > 1`\n84\t  - [ ] Test: Header omits lane count when `laneCount` is 1 or undefined\n85\t  - [ ] Test: Header shows total cost across lanes\n86\t\n87\t## Dev Notes\n88\t\n89\t### Architecture Constraints\n90\t\n91\t- **Architecture Decision 8** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): The Ink render tree gains a `LaneContainer` component that manages lane layout. Each lane is a `Lane` component wrapping existing `WorkflowGraph` + `StoryProgress`. The renderer receives events from all active lanes and routes them by lane ID.\n92\t- **TUI Boundary** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): TUI receives `LaneEvent` objects from the lane pool. Does NOT manage lanes or worktrees. Layout logic is purely presentational — responds to terminal width.\n93\t- **Single Ink instance**: All lanes feed into the same Ink render loop. No multiple Ink instances — that would break terminal rendering.\n94\t- **NFR2**: Multi-lane TUI must render at 15 FPS with up to 4 concurrent lanes. Keep component rendering lightweight.\n95\t\n96\t### What This Story Actually Does\n97\t\n98\tThis story creates the **multi-lane TUI layout layer** — two new Ink components (`Lane`, `LaneContainer`) that present multiple concurrent epic executions in the terminal. It:\n99\t\n100\t1. **Renders** multiple lanes side-by-side, stacked, or single depending on terminal width\n101\t2. **Collapses** overflow lanes (3+) to one-line summaries\n102\t3. **Preserves** single-lane backward compatibility (zero visual change at `max_parallel: 1`)\n103\t4. **Extends** the Header to show lane count and total cost\n104\t5. **Integrates** into the existing `ink-app.tsx` render tree conditionally\n105\t\n106\tThis is a pure presentational story — no lane management, no worktree operations, no event routing (that's 20-3).\n107\t\n108\t### Key Files to Create\n109\t\n110\t| File | Why |\n111\t|------|-----|\n112\t| `src/lib/ink-lane.tsx` | New — single lane display component |\n113\t| `src/lib/ink-lane-container.tsx` | New — multi-lane layout manager with CollapsedLanes |\n114\t| `src/lib/__tests__/ink-lane.test.tsx` | Tests for Lane component |\n115\t| `src/lib/__tests__/ink-lane-container.test.tsx` | Tests for LaneContainer and CollapsedLanes |\n116\t\n117\t### Key Files to Modify\n118\t\n119\t| File | Why |\n120\t|------|-----|\n121\t| `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` | Integrate LaneContainer into the render tree |\n122\t| `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` | Extend SprintInfo/Header with lane count |\n123\t\n124\t### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n125\t\n126\t| File | Why |\n127\t|------|-----|\n128\t| `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx` | `WorkflowGraph` component — embedded inside each Lane |\n129\t| `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` | Activity display components — remain below LaneContainer |\n130\t| `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` | `RendererHandle`, `RendererState` — drives re-renders |\n131\t| `src/lib/lane-pool.ts` | `LaneEvent`, `Lane`, `LaneStatus` — event types consumed by TUI |\n132\t| `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` | `SprintInfo`, `RendererState`, `StoryStatusEntry` — existing types |\n133\t\n134\t### Component Hierarchy (Target State)\n135\t\n136\t```\n137\t<App>\n138\t  <Header />                       ← MODIFY: add lane count\n139\t  <LaneContainer>                  ← NEW: layout manager\n140\t    <Lane epic={10}>               ← NEW: per-epic view\n141\t      <WorkflowGraph />            ← EXISTING: reused inside Lane\n142\t      <StoryProgress />            ← Inline in Lane\n143\t    </Lane>\n144\t    <Lane epic={14}>\n145\t      <WorkflowGraph />\n146\t      <StoryProgress />\n147\t    </Lane>\n148\t    <CollapsedLanes />             ← NEW: one-line summaries for 3+\n149\t  </LaneContainer>\n150\t  <Separator />\n151\t  <CompletedTools />               ← EXISTING: activity section unchanged\n152\t  <ActiveTool />\n153\t  <LastThought />\n154\t  <RetryNotice />\n155\t</App>\n156\t```\n157\t\n158\t### Existing Patterns to Follow\n159\t\n160\t- **Component file naming**: `ink-{name}.tsx` — pure presentational components.\n161\t- **Import style**: `import React from 'react'` + `import { Text, Box } from 'ink'` — standard Ink pattern throughout codebase.\n162\t- **ESM imports**: Use `.js` extensions in TypeScript ESM imports (`'./ink-components.js'`).\n163\t- **Type exports**: Types go at top of component file. Example: `ink-components.tsx` exports all types, then components.\n164\t- **No hooks**: Existing components are stateless (state comes from parent via props). The `Lane` and `LaneContainer` should follow this pattern — pure function components, no `useState` or `useEffect`.\n165\t- **Symbols**: Done `✓`, active `◆`, pending `○` — already used in `StoryBreakdown` and `WorkflowGraph`.\n166\t- **Color scheme**: Use `ink` `<Text color=\"...\">` — green for done, yellow for active, dim for pending. Matches existing `ink-components.tsx`.\n167\t- **Separator**: Reuse `<Separator />` from `ink-components.tsx` between sections.\n168\t\n169\t### Layout Rules (from UX Spec)\n170\t\n171\t| Terminal Width | Layout Mode | Behavior |\n172\t|----------------|-------------|----------|\n173\t| >= 120 cols | side-by-side | Two lanes in columns, each ~half width |\n174\t| 80-119 cols | stacked | Two lanes vertically, compact |\n175\t| < 80 cols | single | One full lane, rest collapsed |\n176\t\n177\t**Lane display format (full):**\n178\t```\n179\t Lane 1: Epic 10 — Driver Interface\n180\t 10-3 ◆ dev (AC 4/9)\n181\t ✓ 10-1  ✓ 10-2  ◆ 10-3  ○ 10-4  ○ 10-5\n182\t claude-code | $4.20 / 18m\n183\t```\n184\t\n185\t**Collapsed lane format (one-line):**\n186\t```\n187\t Lane 3: Epic 11 — Workflow Schema │ 11-1 ◆ dev │ $0.40 / 2m\n188\t```\n189\t\n190\t### Previous Story (19-2) Intelligence\n191\t\n192\t- Story 19-2 created `epic-flow-executor.ts` (~230 lines) — wiring layer for epic completion. Consumed existing modules.\n193\t- Testing pattern: vitest, `vi.mock`, colocated tests in `src/lib/__tests__/`.\n194\t- ESM module pattern: `.js` extensions in imports, TypeScript ESM.\n195\t- Build: `npm run build`, Test: `npm test`.\n196\t- All tests passed after 19-2 with zero regressions.\n197\t- State builder helpers exist at `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/state-builders.ts`.\n198\t- Ink component testing: use `ink-testing-library` render function. Check existing `src/lib/__tests__/ink-*.test.tsx` patterns.\n199\t\n200\t### Git Intelligence\n201\t\n202\tRecent commits:\n203\t- `a5d5ceb feat: story 19-2-epic-flow-execution` — epic flow execution module\n204\t- `2a6f637 feat: story 19-1-epic-completion-detection` — epic completion detection\n205\t- `6c245cb feat: story 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation` — cross-worktree test validation\n206\t- `5d78b76 feat: story 18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution` — merge agent\n207\t- `39582ec feat: story 18-1-merge-serialization-execution` — worktree merge with mutex\n208\t\n209\tAll epic 17-19 modules are complete. This story starts Epic 20 (Multi-Lane TUI).\n210\t\n211\t### Edge Cases\n212\t\n213\t- **Zero lanes**: Should not render `LaneContainer` at all — fall back to existing layout.\n214\t- **One lane**: Render existing single-lane TUI identically (backward compat).\n215\t- **Terminal width exactly 120**: Side-by-side mode (inclusive boundary).\n216\t- **Terminal width exactly 80**: Stacked mode (inclusive boundary).\n217\t- **Terminal width < 40**: Degenerate case — render single lane, truncate long strings.\n218\t- **Lane with very long epic title**: Truncate to fit available width with `…`.\n219\t- **Story progress bar with 10+ stories**: May need to wrap or abbreviate for narrow terminals.\n220\t- **Cost = 0 or null**: Display `$0.00` or `--` respectively.\n221\t- **Elapsed time > 1 hour**: Format as `1h 12m` not `72m`.\n222\t\n223\t### Boundary: What This Story Does NOT Include\n224\t\n225\t- **Lane event routing** — That's story 20-3.\n226\t- **Summary bar** — That's story 20-2.\n227\t- **Merge status display** — That's story 20-2.\n228\t- **Activity display lane filtering** — That's story 20-3.\n229\t- **Ctrl+L keybinding** — That's story 20-3.\n230\t- **Wiring LaneEvent from lane pool to renderer** — That's story 20-3.\n231\t- **RendererState changes for multi-lane** — Minimal changes here (just adding lane data to state). Full event routing in 20-3.\n232\t\n233\t### Project Structure Notes\n234\t\n235\t- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n236\t- Tests: vitest, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n237\t- ESM modules — use `.js` extensions in imports\n238\t- Build: `npm run build`, Test: `npm test`\n239\t- New `.tsx` files for React/Ink components\n240\t- Keep each new component file focused: `ink-lane.tsx` (~80-120 lines), `ink-lane-container.tsx` (~120-180 lines)\n241\t\n242\t### References\n243\t\n244\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 20.1]\n245\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 8 -- Multi-Lane TUI Architecture]\n246\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-parallel-execution.md#Multi-Lane Live Mode]\n247\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-parallel-execution.md#Layout Rules]\n248\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-parallel-execution.md#Component Architecture]\n249\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-app.tsx]\n250\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx#SprintInfo]\n251\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx#RendererHandle]\n252\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx#WorkflowGraph]\n253\t- [Source: src/lib/lane-pool.ts#LaneEvent]\n254\t\n255\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n256\t## Verification Requirements\n257\t\n258\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/20-1-lane-container-lane-components-proof.md)\n259\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n260\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n261\t\n262\t## Documentation Requirements\n263\t\n264\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n265\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/20-1-lane-container-lane-components.md\n266\t\n267\t## Testing Requirements\n268\t\n269\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n270\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n271\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n272\t\n273\t## Dev Agent Record\n274\t\n275\t### Agent Model Used\n276\t\n277\t{{agent_model_name_version}}\n278\t\n279\t### Debug Log References\n280\t\n281\t### Completion Notes List\n282\t\n283\t### File List\n284\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0c112080-0896-4e32-96a0-f82adec16922","uuid":"3bcc3ca4-c651-4633-9581-062c0d761e19","timestamp":"2026-04-04T02:18:17.857Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/20-1-lane-container-lane-components.md","content":"# Story 20.1: Lane Container & Lane Components\n\nStatus: ready-for-dev\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a user,\nI want to see multiple epic lanes in the TUI during parallel execution,\nso that I can track progress across all active worktrees.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** a new `src/lib/ink-lane.tsx`, **when** imported, **then** it exports a `Lane` React component that accepts `LaneProps` (epicId, epicTitle, currentStory, phase, acProgress, storyProgressEntries, driver, cost, elapsedTime) and renders a single lane's status display. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n2. **Given** a new `src/lib/ink-lane-container.tsx`, **when** imported, **then** it exports a `LaneContainer` React component that accepts `LaneContainerProps` (lanes array, terminalWidth) and renders all lanes according to layout rules. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n3. **Given** a terminal width >= 120 columns and 2 active lanes, **when** `LaneContainer` renders, **then** the two lanes display side-by-side (each lane occupying roughly half the terminal width). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n4. **Given** a terminal width between 80 and 119 columns and 2 active lanes, **when** `LaneContainer` renders, **then** the two lanes display stacked vertically in compact mode. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n5. **Given** a terminal width < 80 columns, **when** `LaneContainer` renders, **then** only the single most recently active lane renders in full, and others collapse to one-line summaries. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n6. **Given** each `Lane` component, **when** rendered, **then** it shows: epic title, current story key + phase, a story progress bar (done/in-progress/pending symbols per story), and driver name + cost/time. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n7. **Given** 3 or more active lanes, **when** `LaneContainer` renders at >= 120 cols, **then** lanes 1 and 2 render in full side-by-side, and lanes 3+ collapse to one-line summaries in the format: `Lane N: Epic Title │ story ◆ phase │ $cost / time`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n8. **Given** `max_parallel: 1` (single lane mode), **when** the TUI renders, **then** the display is visually identical to the current single-lane TUI — no `LaneContainer` wrapper visible, no layout changes. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n9. **Given** a `Lane` component receives a `CollapsedLanes` subcomponent, **when** rendered, **then** `CollapsedLanes` accepts an array of collapsed lane data and renders each as a single line with lane index, epic title, current story, phase, cost, and time. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n10. **Given** the `ink-app.tsx` root component, **when** updated to integrate `LaneContainer`, **then** it conditionally renders `LaneContainer` when `laneCount > 1` or renders the existing single-lane layout when `laneCount <= 1`, preserving backward compatibility. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n11. **Given** the `Header` component in `ink-components.tsx`, **when** multiple lanes are active, **then** the header displays lane count and total cost across all lanes (e.g., `codeharness run | 2 lanes | 47m elapsed | $18.60 spent`). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n12. **Given** the `LaneContainer` component, **when** the terminal is resized, **then** the layout mode (side-by-side, stacked, single) re-evaluates based on the new terminal width. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Create `src/lib/ink-lane.tsx` (AC: #1, #6)\n  - [ ] Define `LaneProps` interface with all required fields\n  - [ ] Define `StoryProgressEntry` type: `{ key: string; status: 'done' | 'in-progress' | 'pending' }`\n  - [ ] Implement `Lane` component rendering epic title, current story + phase, story progress bar, driver + cost/time\n  - [ ] Use `✓` for done stories, `◆` for in-progress, `○` for pending in the progress bar\n  - [ ] Format cost as `$X.XX` and elapsed as `Xm` or `Xh Xm`\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Create `src/lib/ink-lane-container.tsx` (AC: #2, #3, #4, #5, #7, #9, #12)\n  - [ ] Define `LaneContainerProps` with `lanes: LaneData[]`, `terminalWidth: number`\n  - [ ] Define `LaneData` interface capturing all per-lane state for rendering\n  - [ ] Implement layout mode calculation: `side-by-side` (>=120), `stacked` (80-119), `single` (<80)\n  - [ ] Render top 2 lanes in full, lanes 3+ via `CollapsedLanes`\n  - [ ] Implement `CollapsedLanes` sub-component: single-line summaries for overflow lanes\n  - [ ] Listen for terminal resize via `process.stdout.columns` to re-evaluate layout\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Integrate into `ink-app.tsx` (AC: #8, #10)\n  - [ ] Add conditional rendering: if `state.lanes && state.lanes.length > 1`, render `LaneContainer`; else render existing single-lane layout\n  - [ ] Ensure zero visual changes when `laneCount <= 1`\n  - [ ] Import `LaneContainer` from `./ink-lane-container.js`\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Extend Header in `ink-components.tsx` (AC: #11)\n  - [ ] Add optional `laneCount` and `totalCost` fields to `SprintInfo`\n  - [ ] Conditionally render lane count in header when `laneCount > 1`\n  - [ ] Format: `codeharness run | {N} lanes | {elapsed} | ${cost}`\n\n- [ ] Task 5: Write unit tests for `src/lib/__tests__/ink-lane.test.tsx` (AC: #1, #6)\n  - [ ] Test: `Lane` renders epic title\n  - [ ] Test: `Lane` renders current story and phase\n  - [ ] Test: `Lane` renders story progress bar with correct symbols\n  - [ ] Test: `Lane` renders driver name, cost, and elapsed time\n  - [ ] Test: `Lane` exports correct types\n\n- [ ] Task 6: Write unit tests for `src/lib/__tests__/ink-lane-container.test.tsx` (AC: #2-#5, #7, #8, #9, #12)\n  - [ ] Test: side-by-side layout when terminalWidth >= 120 and 2 lanes\n  - [ ] Test: stacked layout when terminalWidth 80-119 and 2 lanes\n  - [ ] Test: single-lane layout when terminalWidth < 80\n  - [ ] Test: lanes 3+ collapse to one-line summaries\n  - [ ] Test: single lane mode renders without container wrapper\n  - [ ] Test: collapsed lane format matches `Lane N: Epic Title │ story ◆ phase │ $cost / time`\n  - [ ] Test: layout mode re-evaluates when terminalWidth changes\n\n- [ ] Task 7: Write unit tests for Header extension (AC: #11)\n  - [ ] Test: Header shows lane count when `laneCount > 1`\n  - [ ] Test: Header omits lane count when `laneCount` is 1 or undefined\n  - [ ] Test: Header shows total cost across lanes\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Architecture Constraints\n\n- **Architecture Decision 8** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): The Ink render tree gains a `LaneContainer` component that manages lane layout. Each lane is a `Lane` component wrapping existing `WorkflowGraph` + `StoryProgress`. The renderer receives events from all active lanes and routes them by lane ID.\n- **TUI Boundary** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): TUI receives `LaneEvent` objects from the lane pool. Does NOT manage lanes or worktrees. Layout logic is purely presentational — responds to terminal width.\n- **Single Ink instance**: All lanes feed into the same Ink render loop. No multiple Ink instances — that would break terminal rendering.\n- **NFR2**: Multi-lane TUI must render at 15 FPS with up to 4 concurrent lanes. Keep component rendering lightweight.\n\n### What This Story Actually Does\n\nThis story creates the **multi-lane TUI layout layer** — two new Ink components (`Lane`, `LaneContainer`) that present multiple concurrent epic executions in the terminal. It:\n\n1. **Renders** multiple lanes side-by-side, stacked, or single depending on terminal width\n2. **Collapses** overflow lanes (3+) to one-line summaries\n3. **Preserves** single-lane backward compatibility (zero visual change at `max_parallel: 1`)\n4. **Extends** the Header to show lane count and total cost\n5. **Integrates** into the existing `ink-app.tsx` render tree conditionally\n\nThis is a pure presentational story — no lane management, no worktree operations, no event routing (that's 20-3).\n\n### Key Files to Create\n\n| File | Why |\n|------|-----|\n| `src/lib/ink-lane.tsx` | New — single lane display component |\n| `src/lib/ink-lane-container.tsx` | New — multi-lane layout manager with CollapsedLanes |\n| `src/lib/__tests__/ink-lane.test.tsx` | Tests for Lane component |\n| `src/lib/__tests__/ink-lane-container.test.tsx` | Tests for LaneContainer and CollapsedLanes |\n\n### Key Files to Modify\n\n| File | Why |\n|------|-----|\n| `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` | Integrate LaneContainer into the render tree |\n| `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` | Extend SprintInfo/Header with lane count |\n\n### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n\n| File | Why |\n|------|-----|\n| `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx` | `WorkflowGraph` component — embedded inside each Lane |\n| `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` | Activity display components — remain below LaneContainer |\n| `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` | `RendererHandle`, `RendererState` — drives re-renders |\n| `src/lib/lane-pool.ts` | `LaneEvent`, `Lane`, `LaneStatus` — event types consumed by TUI |\n| `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` | `SprintInfo`, `RendererState`, `StoryStatusEntry` — existing types |\n\n### Component Hierarchy (Target State)\n\n```\n<App>\n  <Header />                       ← MODIFY: add lane count\n  <LaneContainer>                  ← NEW: layout manager\n    <Lane epic={10}>               ← NEW: per-epic view\n      <WorkflowGraph />            ← EXISTING: reused inside Lane\n      <StoryProgress />            ← Inline in Lane\n    </Lane>\n    <Lane epic={14}>\n      <WorkflowGraph />\n      <StoryProgress />\n    </Lane>\n    <CollapsedLanes />             ← NEW: one-line summaries for 3+\n  </LaneContainer>\n  <Separator />\n  <CompletedTools />               ← EXISTING: activity section unchanged\n  <ActiveTool />\n  <LastThought />\n  <RetryNotice />\n</App>\n```\n\n### Existing Patterns to Follow\n\n- **Component file naming**: `ink-{name}.tsx` — pure presentational components.\n- **Import style**: `import React from 'react'` + `import { Text, Box } from 'ink'` — standard Ink pattern throughout codebase.\n- **ESM imports**: Use `.js` extensions in TypeScript ESM imports (`'./ink-components.js'`).\n- **Type exports**: Types go at top of component file. Example: `ink-components.tsx` exports all types, then components.\n- **No hooks**: Existing components are stateless (state comes from parent via props). The `Lane` and `LaneContainer` should follow this pattern — pure function components, no `useState` or `useEffect`.\n- **Symbols**: Done `✓`, active `◆`, pending `○` — already used in `StoryBreakdown` and `WorkflowGraph`.\n- **Color scheme**: Use `ink` `<Text color=\"...\">` — green for done, yellow for active, dim for pending. Matches existing `ink-components.tsx`.\n- **Separator**: Reuse `<Separator />` from `ink-components.tsx` between sections.\n\n### Layout Rules (from UX Spec)\n\n| Terminal Width | Layout Mode | Behavior |\n|----------------|-------------|----------|\n| >= 120 cols | side-by-side | Two lanes in columns, each ~half width |\n| 80-119 cols | stacked | Two lanes vertically, compact |\n| < 80 cols | single | One full lane, rest collapsed |\n\n**Lane display format (full):**\n```\n Lane 1: Epic 10 — Driver Interface\n 10-3 ◆ dev (AC 4/9)\n ✓ 10-1  ✓ 10-2  ◆ 10-3  ○ 10-4  ○ 10-5\n claude-code | $4.20 / 18m\n```\n\n**Collapsed lane format (one-line):**\n```\n Lane 3: Epic 11 — Workflow Schema │ 11-1 ◆ dev │ $0.40 / 2m\n```\n\n### Previous Story (19-2) Intelligence\n\n- Story 19-2 created `epic-flow-executor.ts` (~230 lines) — wiring layer for epic completion. Consumed existing modules.\n- Testing pattern: vitest, `vi.mock`, colocated tests in `src/lib/__tests__/`.\n- ESM module pattern: `.js` extensions in imports, TypeScript ESM.\n- Build: `npm run build`, Test: `npm test`.\n- All tests passed after 19-2 with zero regressions.\n- State builder helpers exist at `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/state-builders.ts`.\n- Ink component testing: use `ink-testing-library` render function. Check existing `src/lib/__tests__/ink-*.test.tsx` patterns.\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nRecent commits:\n- `a5d5ceb feat: story 19-2-epic-flow-execution` — epic flow execution module\n- `2a6f637 feat: story 19-1-epic-completion-detection` — epic completion detection\n- `6c245cb feat: story 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation` — cross-worktree test validation\n- `5d78b76 feat: story 18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution` — merge agent\n- `39582ec feat: story 18-1-merge-serialization-execution` — worktree merge with mutex\n\nAll epic 17-19 modules are complete. This story starts Epic 20 (Multi-Lane TUI).\n\n### Edge Cases\n\n- **Zero lanes**: Should not render `LaneContainer` at all — fall back to existing layout.\n- **One lane**: Render existing single-lane TUI identically (backward compat).\n- **Terminal width exactly 120**: Side-by-side mode (inclusive boundary).\n- **Terminal width exactly 80**: Stacked mode (inclusive boundary).\n- **Terminal width < 40**: Degenerate case — render single lane, truncate long strings.\n- **Lane with very long epic title**: Truncate to fit available width with `…`.\n- **Story progress bar with 10+ stories**: May need to wrap or abbreviate for narrow terminals.\n- **Cost = 0 or null**: Display `$0.00` or `--` respectively.\n- **Elapsed time > 1 hour**: Format as `1h 12m` not `72m`.\n\n### Boundary: What This Story Does NOT Include\n\n- **Lane event routing** — That's story 20-3.\n- **Summary bar** — That's story 20-2.\n- **Merge status display** — That's story 20-2.\n- **Activity display lane filtering** — That's story 20-3.\n- **Ctrl+L keybinding** — That's story 20-3.\n- **Wiring LaneEvent from lane pool to renderer** — That's story 20-3.\n- **RendererState changes for multi-lane** — Minimal changes here (just adding lane data to state). Full event routing in 20-3.\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n- Tests: vitest, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n- ESM modules — use `.js` extensions in imports\n- Build: `npm run build`, Test: `npm test`\n- New `.tsx` files for React/Ink components\n- Keep each new component file focused: `ink-lane.tsx` (~80-120 lines), `ink-lane-container.tsx` (~120-180 lines)\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 20.1]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 8 -- Multi-Lane TUI Architecture]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-parallel-execution.md#Multi-Lane Live Mode]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-parallel-execution.md#Layout Rules]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-parallel-execution.md#Component Architecture]\n- [Source: src/lib/ink-app.tsx]\n- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx#SprintInfo]\n- [Source: src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx#RendererHandle]\n- [Source: src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx#WorkflowGraph]\n- [Source: src/lib/lane-pool.ts#LaneEvent]\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/20-1-lane-container-lane-components-proof.md)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/20-1-lane-container-lane-components.md\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Agent Model Used\n\n{{agent_model_name_version}}\n\n### Debug Log References\n\n### Completion Notes List\n\n### File List\n","numLines":284,"startLine":1,"totalLines":284}}}
