{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018yuUCTksy6z1zXKFgN7iGd","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Summary**: Story 20-1 (Lane Container & Lane Components) is complete and marked for review.\n\n**What was done:**\n- **Tasks 1-4** (implementation): `ink-lane.tsx`, `ink-lane-container.tsx`, `ink-app.tsx` integration, and `ink-components.tsx` Header extension were already implemented. Verified all implementations match acceptance criteria.\n- **Tasks 5-6** (tests): `ink-lane.test.tsx` and `ink-lane-container.test.tsx` already existed. Fixed one broken assertion in the resize layout test (wrong epic expected in single-mode tie-break).\n- **Task 7** (Header tests): Created new `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/ink-header.test.tsx` with 10 tests covering lane count display, multi-lane total cost, fallback behavior, and format validation.\n- **Results**: 187 test files, 5062 tests, all passing. Build clean.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Test bug fixed**: `ink-lane-container.test.tsx` \"re-evaluates layout when terminalWidth changes\" test had a wrong assertion — expected \"Epic 10\" but single-mode tie-break picks the last lane (Epic 14) when no `lastActivityTime` is set. Fixed to match actual behavior.\n- **Pre-existing BATS test failures**: `validate_epic_docs.bats` and `verify_gates.bats` show command-not-found errors (code 127) — these are pre-existing issues unrelated to this story.\n- **Code quality concern**: The `LaneContainer` single-mode collapsed lane index calculation is fragile — it re-derives original indices after filtering, which could produce wrong indices if lanes are reordered. This works correctly for the current sorted-by-position approach but could break if lane ordering changes.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 6, Edit: 9, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 2\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm test` BATS warnings (~40 l