ngine.test.ts) — not introduced by this story.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 20\n- By tool: Read: 6, Edit: 8, Write: 2, Bash: 7, Grep: 3\n- Largest Bash outputs: tsc --noEmit (~50 lines), vitest --coverage (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 6 unique, 7 total reads (worktree-manager.test.ts read 2x)\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution — code-review (2026-04-04T01:55)\n\n- HIGH: resolveConflicts false positive — unparseable test output (0 passed, 0 failed) treated as success. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: driver: undefined as never would crash at runtime. Fixed via MergeConflictInfo type.\n- MEDIUM: Missing // IGNORE: comments on catch blocks. Fixed.\n- LOW (unfixed): parseTestOutput duplicated between merge-agent.ts and worktree-manager.ts.\n- LOW (unfixed): buildEscalationMessage is private, only tested indirectly.\n- No integration test for full mergeWorktree + onConflict + resolveConflicts pipeline.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 8, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Skill: 1, Glob: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm run test:coverage (~80 lines), vitest run (~40-50 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-04 (session 2)\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — create-story (2026-04-04T02:10)\n\n- workflow.yaml referenced workflow.md but actual file was workflow.yaml — minor discovery step.\n- No _bmad/bmm/config.yaml (was at _bmad/config.yaml) — required extra glob.\n- Risk: runTestSuite output field asymmetry between worktree-manager.ts and merge-agent.ts needs careful handling during extraction.\n- Risk: Telemetry writer dependency may have changed since story 16-3.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 10, Glob: 7, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: git log --oneline -5 (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads\n- Redundant operations: One extra Glob for config path\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — dev-story (2026-04-04T02:18)\n\n- writeMergeTelemetry had to be exported for merge-agent two-phase pattern (validate then write telemetry on success). Story spec didn't explicitly require this but it's needed.\n- Branch coverage 96.42% — uncovered branch is nullish coalescing fallback on err.stdout (Istanbul instrumentation edge case).\n- worktree-manager.test.ts read 4 times due to token limits.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 26\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 10, Edit: 13, Write: 2, Glob: 4\n- Largest Bash outputs: tsc --noEmit (~32 lines), vitest --coverage (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 12 total reads (worktree-manager.test.ts read 4x)\n- Redundant operations: worktree-manager.test.ts chunked reads, one broken edit fix\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — code-review (2026-04-04T02:27)\n\n- HIGH: coverage type mismatch (undefined vs null) across validator, worktree-manager, merge-agent. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Missing maxBuffer on exec could truncate large test output. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Missing stderr capture loses diagnostic info. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Telemetry object not typed against canonical TelemetryEntry. Fixed.\n- LOW (unfixed): parseTestOutput first-match regex could pick per-suite counts.\n- LOW (unfixed): writeMergeTelemetry duplicates NDJSON write logic from telemetry-writer.ts.\n- No integration test for full merge-then-validate flow with real git repo.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 30\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 10, Edit: 16, Grep: 6, Glob: 5, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: vitest run verbose (~50 lines), git diff (~80 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 14 total reads\n- Redundant operations: One redundant glob search for workflow file\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — verification (2026-04-04T02:40)\n\n- `codeharness verify` precondition failure: AGENTS.md was stale for `src/lib` — missing `cross-worktree-validator.ts`. Fixed in parent orchestrator.\n- Coverage for `cross-worktree-validator.ts