{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LF9uJNPtHNwmRNh99eK7QX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 20-1-lane-container-lane-components\n**Files reviewed:** 6 source/test files\n**Issues found:** 2 HIGH, 4 MEDIUM, 2 LOW\n\n### Fixes applied:\n\n1. **H2 (fixed):** Created `src/lib/__tests__/ink-app.test.tsx` — 6 tests covering AC #8 (backward compat), AC #10 (conditional LaneContainer rendering), AC #11 (lane count in header), and edge cases (empty lanes, single lane).\n\n2. **M4 (fixed):** Added thin `─` separator between stacked full lanes in `ink-lane-container.tsx` to visually distinguish lane boundaries in stacked/single modes.\n\n### Post-fix results:\n- **Tests:** 188 files, 5068 tests, all pass, zero regressions\n- **Coverage:** 96.77% overall (target: 90%), all 184 files above 80% per-file floor\n- **Build:** Clean TypeScript compilation\n- **Story status:** Updated to `verifying`\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- **HIGH — H2: No integration tests for ink-app.tsx.** AC #8, #10, #11 had zero test coverage at the App integration level. Fixed: created `src/lib/__tests__/ink-app.test.tsx` with 6 tests.\n- **HIGH — H3: Terminal resize not reactive.** `ink-app.tsx:21` reads `process.stdout.columns` at render time but never subscribes to resize events. AC #12 (layout re-evaluation on resize) is only partially implemented — `LaneContainer` correctly re-evaluates layout from its `terminalWidth` prop, but the prop never updates on resize. This is an architecture concern that belongs to story 20-3 (event routing/wiring), not fixed here.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- **LOW — `truncate` degenerate behavior:** `ink-lane-container.tsx:76` — for `maxLen < 4`, truncation silently drops characters without ellipsis. Unlikely to trigger in practice (min terminal width would be very small).\n- **LOW — `LaneContainer` with single lane shows \"Lane 1:\" label:** If someone passes 1 lane directly to `LaneContainer` in side-by-side/stacked mode, it shows a lane index. Guarded by `ink-app.tsx` which only routes to `LaneContainer` when `laneCount > 1`, so this is a theoretical API misuse issue only.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `ink-app.tsx` now has integration tests, but the stacked-lane separator (new `─` line) is only indirectly covered — no test explicitly asserts the separator character between stacked lanes.\n- No test for the degenerate terminal width < 40 case mentioned in edge cases section of the story.\n- No e2e test for actual terminal resize event propagation (AC #12 only tested via prop changes).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- Circular dependency risk: `ink-components.tsx` re-exports `App` from `ink-app.tsx`, which imports from `ink-lane-container.tsx`. Adding any import from `ink-lane-container.tsx` back to `ink-components.tsx` would create a runtime cycle. The current `import('./ink-lane-container.js').LaneData` in `RendererState` is type-only and safe, but this coupling should be noted for future stories.\n- Terminal resize reactivity (H3) needs to be solved at the renderer/app level in story 20-3, not here. Current implementation is correctly scoped as pure-presentational.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:** None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues resolved.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 10, Edit: 3, Grep: 2, Glob: 2, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): full test suite run (~20 lines visible), story tests run (~10 lines), coverage check (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 13 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: One Edit was immediately reverted (attempted `Separator` import that would cause circular dependency — reverted in next Edit). No other redundant operations."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4c41546972533712 (use SendMessage with to: 'a4c41546972533712' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_to