{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TEzzf5B4zc2dWowNrhzKWs","type":"tool_result","content":"299\t\n300\t### 20-1-lane-container-lane-components — dev-story (2026-04-04T06:18)\n301\t\n302\t- Test bug fixed: `ink-lane-container.test.tsx` \"re-evaluates layout when terminalWidth changes\" test had wrong assertion — expected \"Epic 10\" but single-mode tie-break picks last lane (Epic 14) when no `lastActivityTime` set. Fixed to match actual behavior.\n303\t- Pre-existing BATS test failures: `validate_epic_docs.bats` and `verify_gates.bats` show command-not-found errors (code 127) — pre-existing, unrelated.\n304\t- Code quality concern: `LaneContainer` single-mode collapsed lane index calculation is fragile — re-derives original indices after filtering, could produce wrong indices if lane ordering changes.\n305\t\n306\t## Token Report\n307\t- Total tool calls: 31\n308\t- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 6, Edit: 9, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 2\n309\t- Largest Bash outputs: npm test (~40 lines), vitest run (~10 lines), first test run with failure (~30 lines)\n310\t- Files read: 7 unique, 7 total reads\n311\t- Redundant operations: 7 Edit calls for task checkboxes — could be fewer\n312\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0c112080-0896-4e32-96a0-f82adec16922","uuid":"5884f194-a670-48cf-84b8-787e2f67201a","timestamp":"2026-04-04T02:30:29.280Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"\n### 20-1-lane-container-lane-components — dev-story (2026-04-04T06:18)\n\n- Test bug fixed: `ink-lane-container.test.tsx` \"re-evaluates layout when terminalWidth changes\" test had wrong assertion — expected \"Epic 10\" but single-mode tie-break picks last lane (Epic 14) when no `lastActivityTime` set. Fixed to match actual behavior.\n- Pre-existing BATS test failures: `validate_epic_docs.bats` and `verify_gates.bats` show command-not-found errors (code 127) — pre-existing, unrelated.\n- Code quality concern: `LaneContainer` single-mode collapsed lane index calculation is fragile — re-derives original indices after filtering, could produce wrong indices if lane ordering changes.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 31\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 6, Edit: 9, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 2\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm test (~40 lines), vitest run (~10 lines), first test run with failure (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 7 total reads\n- Redundant operations: 7 Edit calls for task checkboxes — could be fewer\n","numLines":14,"startLine":299,"totalLines":312}}}
