er.test.tsx` — \"exports LaneContainer and related types\" test passes\n\n### AC 3: Side-by-side layout at >= 120 cols with 2 lanes — PASS\n\n- **Code evidence:** `getLayoutMode(120)` returns `'side-by-side'`; LaneContainer renders `<Box flexDirection=\"row\">` in side-by-side mode\n- **Test evidence:** `ink-lane-container.test.tsx` — \"returns side-by-side for width >= 120\" tests both 120 and 200; \"renders side-by-side layout when terminalWidth >= 120 and 2 lanes\" verifies Lane 1 and Lane 2 both appear\n\n### AC 4: Stacked layout at 80-119 cols with 2 lanes — PASS\n\n- **Code evidence:** `getLayoutMode` returns `'stacked'` for 80-119; LaneContainer renders `<Box flexDirection=\"column\">` in stacked mode\n- **Test evidence:** `ink-lane-container.test.tsx` — \"returns stacked for width 80-119\" tests 80, 100, 119; \"renders stacked layout when terminalWidth 80-119 and 2 lanes\" verifies both lanes visible\n\n### AC 5: Single-lane layout at < 80 cols — PASS\n\n- **Code evidence:** `getLayoutMode` returns `'single'` for width < 80; only most recently active lane renders full, rest collapsed\n- **Test evidence:** `ink-lane-container.test.tsx` — \"returns single for width < 80\" tests 79, 40, 1; \"renders single-lane layout when terminalWidth < 80\" verifies most recent lane (Epic 14 with lastActivityTime: 200) renders fully\n\n### AC 6: Lane shows epic title, story key + phase, progress bar, driver + cost/time — PASS\n\n- **Code evidence:** `Lane` component renders: title line (epic id + title), story line (currentStory + phase + acProgress), StoryProgressBar (done/in-progress/pending symbols), driver line (driver + cost + elapsed)\n- **Test evidence:** `ink-lane.test.tsx` — \"renders epic title\" (Epic 10, Driver Interface), \"renders current story and phase\" (10-3, dev), \"renders AC progress\" (AC 4/9), \"renders story progress bar with correct symbols\" (checkmark 10-1, diamond 10-3, circle 10-4), \"renders driver name, cost, and elapsed time\" (claude-code, $4.20, 18m)\n\n### AC 7: 3+ lanes at >= 120 shows lanes 1-2 full, 3+ collapsed — PASS\n\n- **Code evidence:** `LaneContainer` slices first 2 as `fullLanes`, rest mapped to `collapsedLaneData` with laneIndex starting at 3\n- **Test evidence:** `ink-lane-container.test.tsx` — \"collapses lanes 3+ to one-line summaries at >= 120 cols\" (3 lanes at width 140: Lane 1, Lane 2 full; Lane 3 collapsed with \"Event Router\", \"$0.40\"); \"handles 4 lanes with first 2 full and rest collapsed\" (Lane 3, Lane 4 collapsed with costs $1.00, $2.50)\n\n### AC 8: Single lane mode identical to current TUI — PASS\n\n- **Code evidence:** `ink-app.tsx` line 28: `laneCount > 1 ? <LaneContainer ...> : <>` existing single-lane layout (WorkflowGraph + StoryBreakdown + DriverCostSummary). When laneCount <= 1, no LaneContainer is rendered.\n- **Test evidence:** `ink-app.test.tsx` — \"renders single-lane layout when no lanes provided\", \"renders single-lane layout when lanes has 1 entry (AC #8 backward compat)\", \"renders empty lanes array as single-lane layout\" — all pass\n\n### AC 9: CollapsedLanes sub-component renders one-line summaries — PASS\n\n- **Code evidence:** `CollapsedLanes` component at line 83 of `ink-lane-container.tsx` accepts `{ lanes: CollapsedLaneData[] }`, renders format: `Lane N: Epic Title | story diamond phase | $cost / time`\n- **Test evidence:** `ink-lane-container.test.tsx` — \"renders collapsed lane format with pipe separators\" (Lane 3, Workflow Schema, 11-1, dev, $0.40, 2m, pipe character); \"renders multiple collapsed lanes\" (Lane 3 + Lane 4); \"handles null story and phase in collapsed format\" (shows --)\n\n### AC 10: ink-app.tsx conditionally renders LaneContainer when laneCount > 1 — PASS\n\n- **Code evidence:** `ink-app.tsx` line 19: `const laneCount = lanes?.length ?? 0`; line 28: `{laneCount > 1 ? <LaneContainer lanes={lanes!} terminalWidth={terminalWidth} /> : <> ... </>}`\n- **Test evidence:** `ink-app.test.tsx` — \"renders LaneContainer when lanes > 1 (AC #10)\" passes\n\n### AC 11: Header shows lane count and total cost when multiple lanes active — PASS\n\n- **Code evidence:** `ink-components.tsx` line 104-123: `Header` accepts `laneCount` prop; when `laneCount > 1`, pushes `${laneCount} lanes` to header parts; uses `laneTotalCost` when in multi-lane mode\n- **Test evidence:** `ink-header.test.tsx` — \"shows lane count when laneCount > 1\" (contains \"2 lanes\"), \"shows lane count of 3\", \"omits lane count when laneCount is 1\", \"omits lane count when laneCount is undefined\", \"shows total cost across lanes when in multi-lane mode\" ($18.60), \"renders header format with pipes between parts\" (contains \"codeharness run | 2 lanes\")\n- **Also:** `ink-app.test.tsx` — \"shows lane count in header when multi-lane (AC #11)\" passes\n\n### AC 12: Layout re-evaluates when terminal width changes — PASS\n\n- **Code evidence:** `LaneContainer` is a pure function component — layout mode is computed fresh from `terminalWidth` prop on every render. No memoization or cached layout state. When parent passes new `terminalWidth`, layout recalculates.\n- **Test evidence:** `ink-lane-container.test.tsx` — \"re-evaluates layout when terminalWidth changes\": renders at width 140 (side-by-side, Lane 1 + Lane 2), then at width 60 (single mode, only Epic 14 fully rendered). Both assertions pass.\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Description | Result |\n|----|-------------|--------|\n| 1 | Lane component file and exports | PASS |\n| 2 | LaneContainer component file and exports | PASS |\n| 3 | Side-by-side layout >= 120 cols | PASS |\n| 4 | Stacked layout 80-119 cols | PASS |\n| 5 | Single-lane layout < 80 cols | PASS |\n| 6 | Lane displays all required info | PASS |\n| 7 | 3+ lanes: first 2 full, rest collapsed | PASS |\n| 8 | Single lane mode backward compatible | PASS |\n| 9 | CollapsedLanes sub-component | PASS |\n| 10 | ink-app.tsx conditional rendering | PASS |\n| 11 | Header lane count and total cost | PASS |\n| 12 | Layout re-evaluates on resize | PASS |\n\n**Final Result: ALL_PASS (12/12 ACs)**\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3329,"cache_read_input_tokens":48419,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3329,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tp1EiHuLRgwUdvr7VPq3jn","session_id":"0c112080-0896-4e32-96a0-f82adec16922","uuid":"64e51548-a02e-453f-814d-ad04b24816b5"}
